	It was a cold night.  Clouds hid the moon completely.  Catherine left the castle.  She liked the dark.\
\cf3 	The castle guards followed her, of course.  She \ul was\ulnone  a princess, after all.  And it wasn't as if she was trying to remain hidden, anyway.  If it were up to the guards, she would be dressed head-to-toe in black, invisible to the casual passerby.  Instead, she was wearing the usual white dress, which caught any light and shone it out like a giant lantern.  In the dark, her pale skin shone almost as bright.  It was odd, her skin had lately turned an unhealthy white color, and while she was advised by those around her to get out in the sun more, she refused and avoided it at all costs.  Nighttime walks, however, became more and more frequent.\
	Catherine did not like the guards.  They followed her everywhere, as if they were spying on her rather than protecting her.  Soon, she would stop their 'protection'.  She could protect herself.\
	She walked the castle for an hour or so, then went to bed.  The guards remained outside her door.\
